## Experience

- **Founder, After School Records** (2023–Present)  
  Built an independent music and technology platform focused on artist ownership and fan engagement. Worked hands-on with web3 technologies, including writing smart contracts for music distribution and experimenting with blockchain-based community and revenue models. Combined product thinking, engineering, and creative strategy.

- **Product Designer, Meta** (2019–2021)  
  Worked on "Lift Testing", a Meta Ads A/B testing tool used by Meta's largest advertisers. Partnered closely with product managers, engineers, and researchers to simplify complex Lift Results dashboards and make Lift Tests as actionable as possible. Focused on system-level thinking, usability at scale, and cross-functional execution.

- **Design CoLab Fellow, IDEO** (2019)  
  Led research-driven design work across ambiguous problem spaces, translating human insights into product strategies, prototypes, and shippable concepts. Bridged design and engineering through prototyping, systems thinking, and storytelling. Specialized in turning complex, undefined problems into structured product solutions.

- **Product Design Intern, Meta** (2018)  
  Worked on Meta Ads' Delivery, specifically the Campaign Budget Optimization feature. Shipped growth tactics to increase adoption of CBO, making it an industry standard. Collaborated with Engineers, Product Managers, and Product Marketing Managers.

- **Software Engineering Intern, Instagram** (2017)  
  Worked in an engineering role focused on building production systems, collaborating with designers and product teams. Developed strong foundations in technical architecture, developer workflows, and cross-functional product development.

- **Independent Music Producer & Artist** (2021–Present)  
  Producing hip-hop and R&B music daily for multiple years. Active creator on Patreon, building a community-supported creative practice with recurring revenue. Uses platforms like Splice, Logic Pro, and digital distribution tools daily, developing deep user empathy for creator platforms.

Project: Design System for Meta Ads' Lift
URL: NA
Summary: A design system for an ever-expanding Meta Ads product.
Context: Lift is a Meta Ads product used by Meta's largest advertisers to A/B test ad strategies.
Skills: product design, design systems, enterprise design, cross-functional collaboration, design collaboration, design documentation, design handoffs, b2b design
Solution: A scalable, adaptable, well-documented design system with a mix of custom components and components inherited from the larger Meta Ads design system. The Lift Results Design System, a living document with code-ready components.
Evidence: Shows product design and design engineering skills through shipping production-ready design system components, achieving 90% compliance rate, and improving UX quality metrics.

Project: Prototyping Mesh: An Open Financial System for IDEO's CoLab
URL: NA
Summary: A proposed community-wide mesh network for peer-to-peer transactions in low-connectivity scenarios.
Context: The IDEO CoLab is a branch of the legendary IDEO company, focused on prototyping emerging technologies in collaboration with a portfolio of companies and a network of design technologists and policy-makers.
Skills: product design, rapid prototyping, mesh networking, emerging technologies, prototyping, community design, community economics, community networks, community systems, community infrastructure, community resilience engineering, community resilience design
Solution: A proposed community-wide mesh network, with Raspberry Pi nodes communicating through Bluetooth protocols. This network allows for peer-to-peer transactions by creating a shared ledger that is uploaded to utility vehicles (such as US Postal Service trucks), which then download the ledger transactions to their appropriate financial institutions upon reaching an area of higher internet connectivity.
Evidence: Shows product design skills through prototyping emerging technologies and designing solutions for complex, future-facing problems in collaboration with cross-disciplinary experts.

AI project. Artificial intelligence, machine learning, LLM, RAG. Andrés's AI experience.
Project: Confidant - Offline AI Assistant
URL: NA
Summary: An open-source, privacy-first AI assistant that provides offline AI health consultation. All processing happens locally with no network access for queries.
Context: Confidant is an AI assistant optimized for health and legal questions, running completely offline using local LLMs and RAG over a knowledge base.
Skills: product design, full-stack development, RAG, AI integration, privacy engineering, local LLM, vector embeddings, desktop development, Rust, TypeScript, React, Python, health technology, legal technology
Solution: A fully offline AI assistant that runs optimized LLM models (Mistral-7B-Instruct, Llama-3.2-3B) locally via llama.cpp, with RAG capabilities using ChromaDB and sentence-transformers. All processing happens client-side with no network access.
Evidence: Shows product design, full-stack development, AI integration, and privacy engineering skills through building a complete offline AI assistant with local LLM inference, RAG capabilities, and desktop app architecture.

Project: Agentic Portfolio Website
URL: https://andresma.com
Summary: A Windows XP-themed portfolio website with a RAG-powered AI agent that answers questions about Andrés's work and experience, using vector embeddings and retrieval-augmented generation.
Context: A portfolio site that demonstrates both design and engineering skills through a nostalgic Windows XP interface, combined with modern AI capabilities.
Skills: product design, design engineering, full-stack development, RAG, AI integration, vector embeddings, Next.js, TypeScript, React, UI/UX design, creative technology
Solution: A portfolio that combines a nostalgic, interactive Windows XP UI with a RAG-powered AI agent. The agent has access to resume content and project details through vector embeddings, allowing it to answer questions, cite specific projects, and point to evidence of skills.
Evidence: Shows product design, design engineering, and full-stack development skills through building a complete portfolio site with AI integration, RAG implementation, vector embeddings, and a cohesive Windows XP-themed UI.
